parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, stalling, and loss of control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
the instrument cluster lights flash on and off
the warning chimes sound
the illumination for the radio and other components flash on and off
loud clicking noise from under the hood
and the vehicle stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle body issues can cause the vehicle to idle race, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle idles at high RPM
the vehicle takes off on its own
and the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress and corrosion can cause electrical system failures, leading to fires, stalling, and loss of control.
symptoms: The electrical junction box corrodes
the instrument cluster lights flash on and off
the warning chimes sound
and the vehicle stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause overheating, leading to engine damage and stalling.
symptoms: The cooling fan won't turn off
and the vehicle overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks can cause electrical system failures, leading to fires, stalling, and loss of control.
symptoms: The roof hatch leaks
and water enters the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of parts for the Takata airbag recall can leave vehicles with potentially deadly airbag defects, putting drivers and passengers at risk of serious injury or death.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are unavailable
delay in repair
concern about safety
inability to sell or trade vehicle due to outstanding recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of accountability from manufacturers can lead to a lack of trust in the safety and reliability of their products, causing frustration and concern for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Feeling of unfairness
concern about manufacturer's integrity
perceived lack of responsibility for potential damage during recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank filling issues can cause fuel to erupt or spill out of the fuel tank filler, leading to a potential fire hazard, and making it difficult or impossible to fill the tank properly.
symptoms: Fuel spills or erupts out of the fuel tank filler when the tank is nearly full
the fuel tank takes an abnormally long time to fill
the fuel tank does not fill up properly
gas shoots out of the filler neck when the tank is nearly full.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission oil cooler can cause the vehicle to leak transmission fluid, leading to premature wear on the transmission and potentially causing it to fail, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil leak from the transmission area
transmission fluid dripping onto the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle pinion nut can cause the vehicle to lurch and thump during braking at low speeds, which can lead to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Lurching and thumping during braking at low speeds
unusual noises or vibrations from the rear axle.
